Love is the good, which, by being diffuſed, is corrupted; ſhe that loves one, another and a thrid;


takes in men at the coyle, and loves onely for her pleaſure. The object of true love is but one: From the Infancy of Time to her decrepitude, the love between two hath been held moſt honorable▪ 
